Job.JobDescription:
Springfield School Dist. is looking for a Basketball Head Varsity Coach to join our program. Apply now.

Springfield Public Schools is committed to finding the best candidate for the job, including candidates who may come from less traditional professional backgrounds. Studies have shown that women and people of color are less likely to apply for jobs unless they believe they meet every one of the qualifications as described in the job posting. We encourage you to apply, even if you do not believe you meet every one of the qualifications outlined in the job posting.
If you are unsure whether you meet the qualifications of this position, or how this would be determined, please feel free to contact Human Resources to discuss your application.
About the District
Springfield Public Schools is located in Springfield, Oregon, in the heart of the Willamette Valley, and serves 185 square miles of the city of Springfield and East/Central Lane County.  We are directly to the East of Eugene, where the University of Oregon is located.  We currently have approximately 10,000 students, over 1,400 staff members and over 600 teachers in our kindergarten through grade 12 school district.  Springfield Public Schools believes student success is our most important outcome.  The success of our students depends on the collective community coming together to support
“Every Student, Every Day”
throughout their K-12 education.
About the Position
Springfield Public Schools seeks outstanding candidates for the position of Varsity Head Girls Basketball Coach at Thurston High School.  To support this work, successful candidates will possess the following characteristics that support our vision of
Every Student, Every Day
and share our values:
A belief that every student can and will learn;
The desire to eliminate inequities in student achievement;
The motivation to foster safe, healthy and engaging environments;
A commitment to promote an inclusive culture that draws on the assets of students, staff and community.
Successful candidates will possess the following qualifications:
Previous High School basketball coaching experience;
Effective communication skills;
Work schedule that allows for flexibility with practice and game schedules;
NFHS/OSAA certified and First Aid certified;
Willingness to work within the school and athletic guidelines;
Ability to organize a complete basketball program grades 9-12;
Ability and commitment to practice cultural competency and demonstrate respect for diversity.
Fundraising knowledge and/or capabilities;
Ability to be District Van Certified;
Understanding of OSAA rules and regulations;
Ability to work with parents and booster clubs.

Springfield School Dist. is looking for an Assistant Coach to join our program. Apply now.

Springfield Public Schools seeks outstanding candidates for assistant coaches for the following Spring sports at Springfield High School:
Baseball
Softball
Track & Field
Golf
Tennis
Activity Leader
Successful candidates will possess the following qualifications:
Coaching experience at the high school level in the sport/activity for which your are applying;
Knowledge of and experience in the sport/activity for which you are applying;
Ability and experience working with high school students;
Ability and experience working with parents, fellow coaches and school district staff;
Effective and positive communication skills;
Ability to work within school district guidelines and budget;
Valid First Aid card;
Availability for daily practices and matches;
Fundraising knowledge and/or capabilities;
Understanding of OSAA rules and regulations;
Good organizational skills;
Ability to pass a pre-employment drug screen and criminal background check;
Ability and commitment to practice cultural competency and demonstrate respect for diversity.
Salary:
Stipend will be based on the type of sport/activity and your previous paid assistant coaching/activity leading experience in the sport/activity for which you are applying.

Woonsocket Public Sch. is looking for a Basketball coach to join our program. Apply now.

POSITION PURPOSE:
The position of Assistant Coach is responsible conducting his/her team activities within the policies and regulation established by the WIAA, KINGCO, and the Bellevue School district.
COMMITMENT TO EQUITY:
The Bellevue School District is committed to a diverse workforce representative of our students, one that embraces and models cultural competency as an international community.
DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES:
(These duties are a representative sample; position assignments may vary.)
• Support the high school in its entire program and strive to improve his/her professional relations with the educational system as well as the coaching profession;
• Be loyal to and support the head coach in conducting the athletic program of that particular sport;
• Be fully aware of the number of games, matches, etc., as specified by the WIAA;
• Assume any duties assigned to him/her by the head coach pertaining to the overall athletic program of that particular sport;
• Assist the Head Coach in all matters relative to the sports season;
• Accompany and direct the assigned team to all games and practices;
• Assume the responsibilities of the Head Coach in the absence of the Head Coach if so designated;
• Be accountable to the Head Coach, Athletic Director, and Principal.  Any questions should be directed to any of them;
• Comply with WIAA coaching clock hour program;
• Assume all other responsibilities as may be assigned.
REPORTING RELATIONSHIPS:
• Reports to and is directly supervised by the Head Coach or the Athletic Director.
EDUCATION & EXPERIENCE
(positions in this class typically require):
Required:
• High School diploma or equivalent.
• Must be at least 19 years of age.
• Hold a current first aid and CPR card, proof of valid first aid and CPR cards must be provided prior to job offer.
LICENSING REQUIREMENTS
(positions in this class typically require):
• None

... Find more information at: https://www.schoolspring.com/?jobid=5608175

Woonsocket Public Sch. is looking for a Flag Football coach to join our program. Apply now.

GENERAL STATEMENT OF RESPONSIBILITIES:
Responsible for assisting in overall strength and positive direction of program; assists in providing for the welfare and safety of all student athletes; work with student athletes, teachers, and counselors to ensure academic progress of the participants; and be an integral part of the school system and the educational program encouraging academic achievement.
PRINCIPAL DUTIES:
Implement program philosophy and strategies consistent with guidelines established by Head Coach;
Assist head coach in promoting program within the District, community and media;
Assist head coach in providing written rules/expectations to student athletes and their parents and enforce these fairly among all participants;
Be knowledgeable of and enforce school, District , AIA and/or league rules, regulations, procedures and policies;
Direct supervision of student athletes in practice areas, locker rooms, buses and at all times on away trips;
Assist in planning and monitoring organized practices that will include proper conditioning, warm-ups and instructions of fundamentals;
Develop athletes to the highest degree of skill and integrity possible;
Model respectful behavior and promote the guidelines of
Pursuing Victory with Honor
;
Follow the approved Athletic Handbook policies and procedures;
Follow all Governing Board policies, in particular as it relates to staff conduct with students and fund raising activities;
Work as a team player with other coaches and the All-Sports Booster Club;
Assist head coach with inventory of equipment and uniforms; and
Other duties as assigned.
QUALIFICATIONS:
PREFERRED EDUCATION, TRAINING AND EXPERIENCE
Current AZ teacher certificate, preferred;
Must hold current CPR/first aid certification;
Must hold current AIA coaching certification;
Demonstrated organizational skills;
Ability to work cooperatively with staff, student athletes, officials and media to promote a positive image of District activity;
Demonstrated ability to relate effectively with staff, students and parents; and
Such alternatives as the Governing Board may find appropriate, acceptable and reasonable.
PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS
Must be able to demonstrate/model appropriate techniques for sport.
